# Phase 2: Test Reorganization TODO

**Goal:** Reorganize tests by type (unit/integration/e2e/property/performance) for clear separation and parallel development

**Current State After Phase 1:**

- ✅ Consolidated common test utilities in `tests/common/`
- ✅ Eliminated duplicate TestEnvironment implementations
- ❌ Tests still scattered across flat structure (api_endpoint_tests.rs, integration_test.rs, etc.)
- ❌ Mixing unit/integration/e2e tests in same files
- ❌ integration_test.rs has circular dependency (imports other test modules)

---

## Task Breakdown

### 1. Create Directory Structure

**Priority:** HIGH - Required foundation
**Estimate:** 15 minutes

Create the new test directory hierarchy:

```
tests/
├── common/              # ✅ Already exists from Phase 1
├── unit/               # NEW - Fast tests, no I/O
│   ├── domain/
│   ├── application/
│   └── infrastructure/
├── integration/        # NEW - DB + storage tests
│   ├── use_cases/
│   ├── repositories/
│   └── storage/
├── e2e/               # NEW - Full API tests
│   ├── api/
│   └── security/
├── property/          # NEW - Property-based tests
│   └── domain/
└── performance/       # NEW - Performance regression guards
```

**Commands:**

```bash
cd rust/tests
mkdir -p unit/{domain,application,infrastructure}
mkdir -p integration/{use_cases,repositories,storage}
mkdir -p e2e/{api,security}
mkdir -p property/domain
mkdir -p performance
```

**Acceptance Criteria:**

- [x] All directories created
- [x] Directory structure matches plan
- [x] `mod.rs` files for `property` and `performance` created
- [ ] No files created yet (just directories)

**Status:** ✅ Done — directories & base `mod.rs` added (commit c43ba9d). Top-level wrappers added and committed (commit db5373a).

