### 12. Update Documentation

**Priority:** MEDIUM - Help developers understand new structure
**Estimate:** 20 minutes

**Actions:**

1. Update `rust/tests/README.md` (or create it) to document:
   - New directory structure
   - How to run tests by category
   - Guidelines for where to put new tests
   - Common utilities location

2. Update root `README.md` testing section

**Example Content:**

```markdown
# Test Organization

## Structure

- `tests/unit/` - Fast unit tests, no I/O (domain logic, validation)
- `tests/integration/` - Integration tests with DB/storage (use cases, repositories)
- `tests/e2e/` - End-to-end API tests (full stack)
- `tests/property/` - Property-based tests (proptest)
- `tests/performance/` - Performance regression guards
- `tests/common/` - Shared test utilities

## Running Tests

# All tests
cargo test

# By category
cargo test --test unit_tests
cargo test --test integration_tests
cargo test --test e2e_tests
cargo test --test property_tests
cargo test --test performance_tests

# Specific test
cargo test test_name
```

**Acceptance Criteria:**

- [ ] README created/updated in tests directory
- [ ] Root README updated
- [ ] Examples accurate and working

